#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:16
msgid "The mirror tool mirrors a selection across a selected axis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:18
msgid ""
"The mirror tool in *Edit* mode is similar to :doc:`Mirroring in Object mode "
"</modeling/meshes/editing/duplicating/mirror>`. It is exactly equivalent to "
"scaling by -1 vertices, edges or faces around one chosen pivot point and in "
"the direction of one chosen axis, only it is faster/handier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:24
msgid ""
"After this tool becomes active, select an axis to mirror the selection on "
"entering x,y, or z."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:26
msgid ""
"You can also interactively mirror the geometry by holding the :kbd:`MMB` and"
" dragging in the direction of the desired mirror direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:31
msgid "Axis of symmetry"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:33
msgid ""
"For each transformation orientation, you can choose one of its axes along "
"which the mirroring will occur."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:36
msgid ""
"As you can see, the possibilities are infinite and the freedom complete: you"
" can position the pivot point at any location around which we want the "
"mirroring to occur, choose one transformation orientation and then one axis "
"on it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:42
msgid "Pivot point"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:44
msgid ""
":doc:`Pivot points "
"</editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/index>` must be set"
" first. Pivot points will become the center of symmetry. If the widget is "
"turned on it will always show where the pivot point is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:49
msgid ""
"On (*Mirror around the Individual Centers ...*) the pivot point default to "
"**median point of the selection of vertices** in *Edit* mode. This is a "
"special case of the *Edit* mode as explained on the :doc:`pivot point page "
"</editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/index>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:58
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:76
msgid "Mesh before mirror."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:64
msgid "Mesh after mirrored along X axis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:67
msgid ""
"On (*Mirror around the 3D Cursor ...*) the pivot point is the *3D Cursor*, "
"the transformation orientation is *Local*, a.k.a. the Object space, and the "
"axis of transformation is X."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:82
msgid "Mesh after mirrored along X axis using the 3d cursor as a pivot point"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:86
msgid "Transformation orientation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:88
msgid ""
":doc:`Transformation Orientations "
"</editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/transform_orientations>` are "
"found on the 3D area header, next to the *Widget* buttons. They decide which"
" coordinate system will rule the mirroring."
msgstr ""
